70.4	Okapi	Okapi	The okapi ( ), Okapia johnstoni, is a giraffid artiodactyl mammal native to the Ituri Rainforest, located in the northeast of the Democratic Republic of the Congo, in Central Africa. Although the okapi bears striped markings reminiscent of zebras, it is most closely related to the giraffe.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Okapia_johnstoni_-Marwell_Wildlife%2C_Hampshire%2C_England-8a.jpg/220px-Okapia_johnstoni_-Marwell_Wildlife%2C_Hampshire%2C_England-8a.jpg
